p: Regarding amino acids, ADCs of methionine and tryptophan were significantly lower in the N. oculata co-product (64% and 56%) than in the N. oculata whole cells (88% and 87%). We found the lowest ADC values of isoleucine, threonine, and valine in N. oculata co-product, compared with Na whole cells. However, we found higher ADC values of arginine, histidine, lysine, leucine, and phenylalanine in N. oculata co-product than in N. oculata whole cells ( Table 10).
